rComments: Such a nice teacher! She is very insightful and gives good feedback for your essays. 5 essays total- one of them is a revision. The lectures are long but they are interesting and helpful for your essays. Take her! One time, she rated our essays based on how "on fleek" they were. She's cool.
Lectures are really boring, readings are always long. 5 essays total, two of which are revised versions of the first two. No final, no midterm, no quizzes. Class seems like a waste of time sometimes.

Zeb's feedback on essay writing is very helpful. Her class is fairly easy with minimal work. However, class discussions can get boring  when she lets outspoken students continue to speak like there is no tomorrow rather than trying to engage the whole class.

Lectures were confusing at times, but Zeb was very friendly and amenable to the class. The readings toward the end of the quarter were the most interesting and the assignments were relatively easy throughout.

Her lectures are a bit confusing, especially when she's using the chalkboard. Don't fall behind on the readings b/c she refers to it constantly. Agreed, she's a hard grader but really puts in the effort for the class and you can see the passion she has for teaching.

The content was a bit dry in the beginning but her teaching style definitely made it bearable. She likes to interact in her lectures and is very willing to meet outside or after class for those who have questions or concerns. She's a tough grader but worth taking.
